      <description>Mary Edith Moody was born on July 29, 1926, in Baton Rouge, La. She
            graduated from Southern University Laboratory School and earned degrees from Southern
            University, Louisiana State University, and the Interdenominational Theological Center
            in Atlanta, Ga. Moody taught English and business education at the Louisiana State
            School for the Blind for more than 30 years. She became a minister in 1972 and has
            served at several African Methodist Episcopal churches in the Baton Rouge
            area.</description>
